				Most recently I led design at [AngelList](http://angel.co "AngelLIst") &mdash; the world’s largest startup community &mdash; where I focused on growing our design team and buildimg our jobs marketplace. Currently, I’m taking some time to travel and reset.  
			
				I’ve been working as a designer for almost 15 years. In that time I’ve designed books, building signage, interfaces, illustrations and more. Like all designers, I dream of one day designing an airplane livery, a chair, and a house. These days, however, I increasingly find myself at the intersection of the ‘product’ and ‘design’	 disciplines.
				
				I got into design by making posters for my friends’ bands and events. Then took a detour through the world of newspaper design. I still love newspapers and think web design can learn a whole lot more from them.

				As a design leader, I tend to be more people-focused than pixel-focused — though that dichotomy is a huge oversimplification. I truly love working with a team to help them identify, manifest and sustain the ideal conditions for their success. If you work with me, we will have ongoing conversation about ‘how you do your best work’.
		
