				### AngelList
			
				I joined AngelList in 2016 with a mission to make finding a job, or conversely making a new hire, a more human experience. Since then we’ve moved the needle in the right direction, but there’s still a lot to be done. 
				
				Soon after joining the company, I became the fouth person in a ‘skunkworks’ team developing an entirely new product offering — <a href="a-list.co">A&ndash;List</a>. Over the next three years, we grew A&ndash;List into a double-digit-million dollar business. That was pretty fun. 
				
				
				One of my proudest acheivements at AngelList is scaling the design team from two to twelve designers and simulataneusly establishing design as a top-level team in the ogranisation. The deisgn team shipped entire new products, relaunches of existing core products and significantly improved the experience of over 10million job seekers.
					
				As part of the executive team, I contributed to product and business strategy, was integral to delivering key product relaunches, and was part of the deal team on two company acquisitions. 	
					
				Apart from my time at AngelList, I’ve had an intentionally varied career &mdash; from journalist, to designer, to growth-marketer, to design manager. I try to bring what I’ve learnt from each stage with me to the next. The consistent threads have been a focus on narrative and on people. 
			
			

