					### Design communities
					Bringing people together to talk about design is something I really enjoy — whether thats a full-scale design event or a small dinner.
	
					Between 2013 and 2015 I ran an event called [Design+Banter](http://designandbanter.com/) with my buddy [Sam](https://twitter.com/thesamwillis). We started it to meet other designers and to get to know the design community in London. It regularly attracted over 200 attendees a month, sold-out in under a minute and featured world-class design speakers from across the globe. With my move to New York on the horizon, we called it a day in late 2015 after twenty successful events.
	
